  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Response and Preparedness South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This intervention will support South Sudanese Red Cross (SSRC) to contribute to prevention of COVID-19 transmission in South Sudan&#x2019;s main hub, Juba. The overall goal of SSRC is to contribute to the prevention and control of COVID-19 community transmission through increased knowledge among health care workers and Red Cross volunteers; and improved preventive COVID-19 hygiene behavior by the vulnerable population.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">South Sudan can expect a massive impact within a matter of weeks if no effective measures are taken early in the COVID-19 outbreak, unless effective suppression and control measures are enacted in all areas with active outbreaks. The risk of further COVID-19 importation to South Sudan has been assessed to be high.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activities included in this response focus on trainings of volunteers on WaSH and Health, hygiene promotion, improving access to safe water and public health awareness raising.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall targeted beneficiaries for this intervention is 85,000.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Juba, South Sudan</narrative>
  </description>
